    "body" : "<p><em>instanceof</em> is a keyword that can be used to test if an object is of a specified type.</p>\n\n<p>Example :</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class MainClass {\n    public static void main(String[] a) {\n\n    String s = \"Hello\";\n    int i = 0;\n    String g;\n    if (s instanceof java.lang.String) {\n       // This is going to be printed\n       System.out.println(\"s is a String\");\n    }\n    if (i instanceof Integer) {\n       // This is going to be printed as autoboxing will happen (int -&gt; Integer)\n       System.out.println(\"i is an Integer\");\n    }\n    if (g instanceof java.lang.String) {\n       // This case is not going to happen because g is not initialized and\n       // therefore is null and instanceof returns false for null. \n       System.out.println(\"g is a String\");\n    } \n} \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here is my <a href=\"http://www.java2s.com/Tutorial/Java/0060__Operators/TheinstanceofKeyword.htm\" rel=\"noreferrer\">source</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 917764,
      "reputation" : 52819,
      "user_id" : 950178,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8d1055cc8972f3b6a116f501f617c7be?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jayendra",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/950178/jayendra"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 74,
    "last_activity_date" : 1399676455,
    "last_edit_date" : 1399676455,
    "creation_date" : 1316770125,
    "answer_id" : 7526895,
    "question_id" : 7526817,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>instanceof</code> is used to check if an object is an instance of a class, an instance of a subclass, or an instance of a class that implements a particular interface.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/op2.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Read more from the Oracle language definition here.</a></p>\n"
